    "RL is a closed-loop system with has a loop connection between the agent and the Fig. 3 Comparison of θ 1 and θ 2 obtained from mathematical and Simscape models of the SLRIP 0 0.5 1 1.5 2 2.5 3 3.5 4 4.5 5 t(s) 0 1 2 3 4 1 (deg) 1 -SimMechanics model without friction 1 -Mathematical model without friction 0 0.5 1 1.5 2 2.5 3 3.5 4 4.5 5 t(s) -20 -10 0 10 20 environment.",
    "A loop can be named a step and an episode has N steps.",
    "The process of training is accomplished based on the step numbers ( N s) and episode numbers ( N e), where ( N s × N e) is the loop time.The connection between the state and the action is linked using a table called Q or Q-table as policy [26].",
    "Each value in the table is noted as Q s i, a j where i = (1, 2, … n), j = (1, 2, … m).",
    "Table 3 illustrates an example of Q-Table."
